-Excuse me, L?

67
00:03:57,737 --> 00:03:59,070
L: Mm.

68
00:03:59,104 --> 00:04:00,637
And from now on, I'll have to
ask that you stop calling me

69
00:04:00,670 --> 00:04:03,137
L. It's Ryuzaki now,
just to be safe.

70
00:04:03,170 --> 00:04:06,070
-Uh, OK, Ryuzaki.

71
00:04:06,104 --> 00:04:08,604
If we know that he needs
a name and a face to kill,

72
00:04:08,637 --> 00:04:10,470
couldn't we cut down on
the number of victims

73
00:04:10,504 --> 00:04:13,037
by keeping criminals'
names from the news?

74
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:15,537
-If we do that, we'll only
be putting the general public

75
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:16,304
at risk.

76
00:04:16,337 --> 00:04:17,304
-The general public?

77
00:04:17,337 --> 00:04:17,804
Why?

78
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:23,437
-Kira is childish
and he hates losing.

79
00:04:23,470 --> 00:04:24,404
-But how do you--

80
00:04:24,437 --> 00:04:26,437
-Just what do you mean?

81
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:30,037
-Well, I'm also childish
and I hate to lose.

82
00:04:30,070 --> 00:04:32,837
That's how I know.

83
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:37,804
-Ryuzaki, would you mind being
a little more specific for us?

84
00:04:37,837 --> 00:04:39,337
-Early on in the
investigation, I

85
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:42,337
tried to provoke Kira
with that broadcast.

86
00:04:42,370 --> 00:04:44,337
Up until then we thought
that Kira would only

87
00:04:44,370 --> 00:04:47,637
go after criminals, but
as we all witnessed,

88
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:50,504
he didn't hesitate
to kill my stand-in.

89
00:04:50,537 --> 00:04:53,504
Also, as soon as I said we knew
he was in the Kanto region,

90
00:04:53,537 --> 00:04:55,637
in defiance he made
sure his next victims

91
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,270
came from within
Japan, as if to say,

92
00:04:58,304 --> 00:04:59,937
and what are you
going to do about it?

93
00:05:02,737 --> 00:05:04,404
He's met each of my
challenges head-on

94
00:05:04,437 --> 00:05:06,104
and he's never
missed an opportunity

95
00:05:06,137 --> 00:05:07,837
to return the favor.

96
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,270
Now what do you
think would happen

97
00:05:09,304 --> 00:05:12,304
if we tried to use media
restrictions to hide criminals

98
00:05:12,337 --> 00:05:14,337
from someone like that?

99
00:05:14,370 --> 00:05:15,737
-I guess--

100
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:18,737
-"If you choose to withhold the
names of your worst criminals,

101
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:21,337
I'll kill petty criminals
or the innocent.

102
00:05:21,370 --> 00:05:24,970
I'm holding the whole world
hostage, so who's it gonna be?

103
00:05:25,004 --> 00:05:27,037
I'm not the evil
one here, but all

104
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,970
those who oppose me
by hiding criminals?

105
00:05:29,004 --> 00:05:32,904
You are truly evil."

106
00:05:32,937 --> 00:05:35,604
[sigh] That's exactly
how Kira thinks.

107
00:05:35,637 --> 00:05:37,170
In any case, let's
look at another way

108
00:05:37,204 --> 00:05:39,804
we can use the media
to draw him out.

109
00:05:39,837 --> 00:05:41,337
-But how?

110
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:43,804
-How about something like this?

111
00:05:43,837 --> 00:05:46,970
"Death of FBI agents
infuriates the US.

112
00:05:47,004 --> 00:05:49,137
Latest killings anger the
international policing

113
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:50,404
community.

114
00:05:50,437 --> 00:05:53,837
Nations agree to send 1,500
investigators to Japan."

115
00:05:53,870 --> 00:05:55,570
For Kira, this will
be way beyond what

116
00:05:55,604 --> 00:05:57,304
he faced with the FBI.

117
00:05:57,337 --> 00:05:59,904
He'll see everyone as
a potential threat.

118
00:05:59,937 --> 00:06:02,070
Psychologically he'll
start to feel cornered,

119
00:06:02,104 --> 00:06:05,804
and that will cause him to take
some kind of drastic action.

120
00:06:05,837 --> 00:06:07,570
-That-- that's interesting.

121
00:06:07,604 --> 00:06:10,337
-So he'll think there are
1,500 when there are really

122
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:11,804
only seven of us.

123
00:06:11,837 --> 00:06:13,937
And since none of these
investigators exists,

124
00:06:13,970 --> 00:06:15,737
Kira won't be able to kill them.

125
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:17,604
-It just might work.

126
00:06:17,637 --> 00:06:19,770
-Well, before we
celebrate, I'll tell you

127
00:06:19,804 --> 00:06:22,370
the rest of my thoughts
on the Kira case.

128
00:06:22,404 --> 00:06:24,337
[all murmur]

129
00:06:24,370 --> 00:06:26,137
-Kira works alone.

130
00:06:26,170 --> 00:06:30,104
He had access to all our
classified information.

131
00:06:30,137 --> 00:06:32,604
-What evidence do you have
that he's working alone?

132
00:06:32,637 --> 00:06:33,904
-Hold on, Aizawa.

133
00:06:33,937 --> 00:06:37,437
Let's listen to his entire
theory before asking questions.

134
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:40,237
-We know he needs a
name and a face to kill,

135
00:06:40,270 --> 00:06:42,804
and to some extent, he can
control a victim's time

136
00:06:42,837 --> 00:06:45,937
of death and their
actions before dying.

137
00:06:45,970 --> 00:06:47,504
We already know that much.

138
00:06:47,537 --> 00:06:50,470
Please keep that
in mind and listen

139
00:06:50,504 --> 00:06:53,637
carefully to what
I have to say next.

140
00:06:53,670 --> 00:06:57,170
On December 14, 12 FBI
investigators enter Japan.

141
00:07:00,937 --> 00:07:03,304
Here we are on December 19.

142
00:07:03,337 --> 00:07:06,370
Using prison inmates,
Kira conducts experiments,

143
00:07:06,404 --> 00:07:09,070
manipulating his victims'
actions before they die.

144
00:07:09,104 --> 00:07:12,104
In other words, during this
window of only five days,

145
00:07:12,137 --> 00:07:14,537
Kira became aware of
the FBI's presence

146
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:17,537
and obviously felt threatened.

147
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:19,670
Because he didn't know any
of their names or faces,

148
00:07:19,704 --> 00:07:21,804
he was at a disadvantage.

149
00:07:21,837 --> 00:07:24,670
He needed to know how much
control he had over his victims

150
00:07:24,704 --> 00:07:27,237
before he could use it
against the 12 agents.

151
00:07:27,270 --> 00:07:30,670
And as we all know,
on December 27--

152
00:07:30,704 --> 00:07:32,670
LIGHT (VOICEOVER): I got
a hold of a file which

153
00:07:32,704 --> 00:07:36,170
contained all the names and
faces of the FBI investigators

154
00:07:36,204 --> 00:07:40,304
in Japan and I succeeded in
killing each one of them.

155
00:07:40,337 --> 00:07:42,370
It's practically
impossible to guess

156
00:07:42,404 --> 00:07:44,604
which agent gave
the file to Kira,

157
00:07:44,637 --> 00:07:47,970
but I have to make sure
that no one ever finds out

158
00:07:48,004 --> 00:07:50,470
that I came into contact
with Raye Pember.

159
00:07:54,204 --> 00:07:55,370
-Huh?

160
00:07:55,404 --> 00:07:57,337
How come you're not using
the Death Note today?

161
00:07:57,370 --> 00:07:59,204
You studying for
those entrance exams?

162
00:07:59,237 --> 00:08:01,037
-Those are the
least of my worries.

163
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:03,237
Plus, it's a little
late to start now.

164
00:08:03,270 --> 00:08:03,804
-Oh?

165
00:08:03,837 --> 00:08:04,737
What you doing?

166
00:08:04,770 --> 00:08:07,970
LIGHT: December
19 to December 27.

167
00:08:08,004 --> 00:08:11,337
I've been most active
during this period.

168
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:13,504
L: During this period, to
the best of our knowledge,

169
00:08:13,537 --> 00:08:17,437
at least 23 individuals
died of heart attacks.

170
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:20,837
But these victims were different
from Kira's previous targets.

171
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:23,204
They were all alleged
criminals, ex-convicts,

172
00:08:23,237 --> 00:08:25,437
or suspects in ongoing
investigations.

173
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:27,570
So legally speaking,
they were innocent.

174
00:08:27,604 --> 00:08:28,770
-That's true.

175
00:08:28,804 --> 00:08:31,137
-What this indicates
is that Kira

176
00:08:31,170 --> 00:08:33,337
had to manipulate these
lesser criminals in order

177
00:08:33,370 --> 00:08:35,704
to kill those FBI agents.

178
00:08:35,737 --> 00:08:37,437
He killed that
many people so we'd

179
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:39,304
be unable to tell
the decoys from those

180
00:08:39,337 --> 00:08:41,004
who were actually used.

181
00:08:41,037 --> 00:08:44,504
In truth, he probably
only needed a few.

182
00:08:44,537 --> 00:08:47,370
He waited eight days so
the FBI could investigate

183
00:08:47,404 --> 00:08:49,870
other suspects, which meant
there'd be no time line linking

184
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:51,370
him to their deaths.

185
00:08:51,404 --> 00:08:54,670
I suspect Kira had to be one of
the people being investigated

186
00:08:54,704 --> 00:08:58,870
by the FBI between the 14th
and the 19th of December.

187
00:08:58,904 --> 00:09:03,037
In fact, I have no doubt.

188
00:09:03,070 --> 00:09:05,304
These are files
provided by the FBI,

189
00:09:05,337 --> 00:09:07,270
and they contain
additional information

190
00:09:07,304 --> 00:09:08,969
you might find useful.

191
00:09:09,002 --> 00:09:10,669
For obvious reasons,
you're not permitted

192
00:09:10,702 --> 00:09:12,336
to take these out
of this room, but--

193
00:09:12,369 --> 00:09:13,702
TOUTA MATSUDA: Amazing!

194
00:09:13,736 --> 00:09:16,402
There might only be five of
us, but with this information

195
00:09:16,436 --> 00:09:18,169
we should be able to
cover a lot of ground.

196
00:09:18,202 --> 00:09:19,569
-We'll split into two teams.

197
00:09:19,602 --> 00:09:21,502
One team traces the FBI agents.

198
00:09:21,536 --> 00:09:23,336
The other looks at the
heart attack victims.

199
00:09:23,369 --> 00:09:25,902
-There weren't that many people
who had access to information

200
00:09:25,936 --> 00:09:28,102
from headquarters, and
of those, the FBI only

201
00:09:28,136 --> 00:09:30,802
investigated a small group
in the first five days.

202
00:09:30,836 --> 00:09:31,302
-Yeah.

203
00:09:31,336 --> 00:09:32,802
Yeah.

204
00:09:32,836 --> 00:09:35,102
-So does anyone
have any questions?

205
00:09:35,136 --> 00:09:35,602
-Uh?

206
00:09:35,636 --> 00:09:36,802
-Uh?

207
00:09:36,836 --> 00:09:40,202
-Actually, Ryuzaki, I do
have one question for you,

208
00:09:40,236 --> 00:09:42,536
and it pertains to what you
said to us earlier about how

209
00:09:42,569 --> 00:09:43,669
you hate to lose.

210
00:09:43,702 --> 00:09:45,302
Is the fact that you've
shown us your face mean

211
00:09:45,336 --> 00:09:46,602
that you've lost?

212
00:09:46,636 --> 00:09:49,469
By just being here, are you
admitting defeat to Kira?

213
00:09:49,502 --> 00:09:50,669
-That's right.

214
00:09:50,702 --> 00:09:52,969
By showing my face to you
now and by sacrificing

215
00:09:53,002 --> 00:09:57,136
the lives of 12 FBI agents,
I have lost the battle.

216
00:09:57,169 --> 00:09:59,436
But I'm not going
to lose the war.

217
00:09:59,469 --> 00:10:02,536
This is the first time I've
ever put my life on the line.

218
00:10:02,569 --> 00:10:04,236
I want to show
Kira that we're all

219
00:10:04,269 --> 00:10:07,802
willing to risk our lives if
that's what it takes-- hmf,

220
00:10:07,836 --> 00:10:11,202
and that justice will
prevail no matter what.

221
00:10:11,236 --> 00:10:12,902
-Hey, yeah, that's right.

222
00:10:12,936 --> 00:10:14,369
-I like the sound of that.

223
00:10:14,402 --> 00:10:15,636
-We can do this.

224
00:10:15,669 --> 00:10:16,402
-All right, then.

225
00:10:16,436 --> 00:10:17,736
Let's do this, Ryuzaki.

226
00:10:17,769 --> 00:10:20,002
SOICHIRO YAGAMI (VOICEOVER):
Well, I had my doubts about

227
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,936
whether it was
really him at first,

228
00:10:21,969 --> 00:10:23,836
but there's no mistaking it.

229
00:10:23,869 --> 00:10:26,302
This man is L.

230
00:10:26,336 --> 00:10:27,802
-Before we go any
further, I have

231
00:10:27,836 --> 00:10:29,836
to be absolutely sure
that none of you are Kira,

232
00:10:29,869 --> 00:10:31,402
so I'll need to speak
with each of you

233
00:10:31,436 --> 00:10:34,036
individually before
you leave today.

234
00:10:34,069 --> 00:10:35,302
-Huh.

235
00:10:35,336 --> 00:10:36,436
What's the deal?

236
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:37,702
He still doesn't trust us?

237
00:10:37,736 --> 00:10:39,969
SOICHIRO YAGAMI: No, I
think it's a fair request.

238
00:10:40,002 --> 00:10:41,869
Try to see it from
his perspective.

239
00:10:41,902 --> 00:10:44,269
Kira's been getting information
from our headquarters

240
00:10:44,302 --> 00:10:46,702
from the very beginning,
so there's a good chance

241
00:10:46,736 --> 00:10:47,569
that he's one of us.

242
00:10:47,602 --> 00:10:48,969
-Chief's right.

243
00:10:49,002 --> 00:10:51,602
Working this case has given us
a chance to see him in person.

244
00:10:51,636 --> 00:10:53,136
-He's risking his
life to be here.

245
00:10:55,769 --> 00:10:57,336
L (VOICEOVER): Things
are going well.

246
00:10:57,369 --> 00:11:02,102
Just one clue, a single
decisive factor's all I need.

247
00:11:02,136 --> 00:11:04,802
LIGHT (VOICEOVER):
Just one oversight.

248
00:11:04,836 --> 00:11:08,569
A single piece of evidence
is all it would take.

249
00:11:08,602 --> 00:11:10,636
It could cost me my life.

250
00:11:10,669 --> 00:11:12,036
BOTH (VOICEOVER):
Just one thing.

251
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:40,864
RYUK: You already
finished studying?

252
00:11:40,897 --> 00:11:42,930
-I guess.

253
00:11:42,964 --> 00:11:44,264
